<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF3DFF77A7ADF8B9FC07DBE9" pageId="164" pageNumber="165" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF3DFF77A7ADF8B9FEF0DB71" blockId="164.[189,310,1878,1904]" box="[189,310,1878,1904]" pageId="164" pageNumber="165">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF3DFF77A7ADF8B9FEF0DB71" bold="true" box="[189,310,1878,1904]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="164" pageNumber="165" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF3DFF77A7ADF8B9FEF0DB71" bold="true" box="[189,310,1878,1904]" pageId="164" pageNumber="165">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF3DFF77A7ADF869FC07DBE9" blockId="164.[189,1400,1926,2025]" pageId="164" pageNumber="165">
This species may be separated from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF3DFF77A42CF869FC6FDBA1" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[828,937,1926,1952]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="164" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF3DFF77A42CF869FC6FDBA1" box="[828,937,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="164" pageNumber="165">Charinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Oceania by means of the following characters: carapace with black markings radiating from fovea, cheliceral claw with five teeth, patella with three ventral spines, median and lateral eyes well developed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
